OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F438A1772745123
OL,3,CCompany admits supplying water that
OL,4,Cwas unfit for human consumption
OL,6,FThe company that provides water for
OL,7,F1.8 million customers across the West
OL,8,FCountry has admitted supplying water
OL,9,Fthat was unfit for human consumption
OL,10,Fin South Devon.
OL,12,FHundreds of people were left unwell
OL,13,Fand four were hospitalised after the
OL,14,Fwater supply was contaminated with the
OL,15,Fparasite cryptosporidium in Brixham in
OL,16,FMay 2024.
OL,18,FAround 17,000 homes and businesses in
OL,19,Fthe area were told to boil their water
OL,20,Fand the notice was not lifted until
OL,21,FJuly 2024.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/11
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
